channel.description:
This will check that your player CHAR is within the correct boundaries. 

[code]public void validCharDesign() { //Developed to make sure player chars will come out ok.
                        if (pHead < 0 ||pHead > 9)
                                        pHead=1;
                        if (pBeard < 10 ||pBeard > 17)        
                                        pBeard=10; 
                        if (pTorso < 18 ||pTorso > 25)
                                        pTorso=18;
                        if (pArms < 26 ||pArms > 32)
                                        pArms=26;
                        if (pHands < 33 ||pHands > 35)
                                        pHands=33;
                        if (pLegs < 36 ||pLegs > 41)
                                        pLegs=36;
                        if (pFeet < 42 ||pFeet > 44)
                                        pFeet=42;                        
                        } else if (pGender == 1) {
                        if (pHead < 45 || pHead > 55)
                                        pHead=50;
                        if (pBeard > 0)
                                        pBeard=1;
                        if (pTorso < 61 || pTorso > 66)
                                        pTorso=57;
                        if (pArms < 67 || pArms > 69)
                                        pArms=62;
                        if (pHands < 70 || pHands > 78)
                                        pHands=68;
                        if (pLegs < 79 || pLegs > 81)
                                        pLegs=72;
                        if (pFeet < 82 || pFeet > 84)
                                        pFeet=80;       
                       }
[/code]

You should call [code]validCharDesign()[/code] wherever you see fit to. I would personally see it fit in [code]initialize()[/code] but if you feel the need to call it anywhere else, feel free to do so.

This shouldn't be needed under normal circumstances, but it could be helpful.
